'''運煤到新堡'''('''taking coal(s) to Newcastle''') 是一句英文的[[熟語|熟語]]，表示有勇無謀的行動或是多此一舉。<ref name="britannica">[http://www.britannica.com/eb/article-9055575/Newcastle-upon-Tyne "Newcastle upon Tyne"], ''Encyclopædia Britannica''</ref> 其典故來由，是因為位於[[英格蘭|英格蘭]]東北部的[[泰恩河畔新堡|泰恩河畔新堡]]，在經濟發展上曾經大量依賴[[煤|煤]]的生產，該地區開採煤礦的歷史起於1538年。<ref name="ne_history">[http://www.northeasthistory.co.uk/the_north_east/history/coal/1100_1500/index.html "Early Coal Mining 1100- 1500"] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070927000000/http://www.northeasthistory.co.uk/the_north_east/history/coal/1100_1500/index.html |date=2007-09-27 }}, ''[[The_Northern_Echo|The Northern Echo]]'s History Pages''</ref><ref name="newcastle_uni">[http://www.ncl.ac.uk/about/history/timeline.phtml "Newcastle timeline"] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070403171508/http://www.ncl.ac.uk/about/history/timeline.phtml |date=2007-04-03 }}, [[Newcastle_University|Newcastle University]]</ref>每年有15,000[[公噸|公噸]]的煤產自此地，<ref name="pitwork">
[https://web.archive.org/web/20071011224545/http://pitwork.net/terrymc%2Bmining.htm "Early Coal Mining"], Terry McKinney, Pitwork.net</ref>是以若是其它地方想要向新堡兜售煤都將無功而返，這是簡單的[[供給和需求|供給和需求]]原理。原文 "To carry Coals to Newcastle" 最早的書面資料，是在1679年的北美，一封由[[:en:William_Fitzhugh|William Fitzhugh]] 所寫的信中"But relating farther to you would be carrying Coals to new Castle."而最早見諸報章則是一篇文章的標題：Labour in vain: or Coals to Newcastle: A sermon to the people of Queen-Hith, 1709.

[[:en:Timothy_Dexter_(businessman)|Timothy Dexter]]是一位[[美國|美國]]的實業家，曾經成功顛覆了這句話的意義。而他向來以古怪形象聞名當代，大眾視其為不入流的丑角。由於商業競爭對手的慫恿，他運了一船的煤並打算在新堡脫手。出乎意料之外，他並沒有如大家所以為的血本無歸，反而大發利市。原來是因為正好遇上當地的礦工罷工，致使新堡的煤礦生產停止，他運來的煤恰好滿足當地的殷切需求。<ref name="knapp">{{cite book | last = Knapp | first = Samuel L. | title = Life of Lord Timothy Dexter: Embracing sketches of the eccentric characters that composed his associates, including "Dexter's Pickle for the knowing ones" | publisher = J.E. Tilton and Company | date = 1858 | location = Boston | url = http://search.abaa.org/dbp2/book204715555.html | deadurl = yes | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20071202095808/http://search.abaa.org/dbp2/book204715555.html | archivedate = 2007-12-02 }}</ref><ref name="nash">{{cite book | last = Nash | first = Jay Robert | title = Zanies, The World's Greatest Eccentrics | publisher = New Century Publishers | date = 1982 | url = http://www.amazon.com/Zanies-eccentrics-Jay-Robert-Nash/dp/0832901237 | ISBN=0-8329-0123-7 }}</ref> 

其它的案例還有1990年，美國國家礦業協會銷售煤到新堡，利潤頗豐。<ref name="stlouis">[http://nl.newsbank.com/nl-search/we/Archivesp_product=SL&p_theme=sl&p_action=search&p_maxdocs=200&p_topdoc=1&p_text_direct-0=0EB04CAF731CB875&p_field_direct-0=document_id&p_perpage=10&p_sort=YMD_date:D "U.S. Beats The Price Of Coal In Newcastle"], William Flannery, ''[[St._Louis_Post-Dispatch|St. Louis Post-Dispatch]]'', May 10, 1990</ref>而2004年時，新堡推動煉[[鋁|鋁]]計畫，亦由[[加拿大鋁業公司|加拿大鋁業公司]]自[[俄羅斯|俄羅斯]]進口70,000公噸低[[硫|硫]]煤至當地。不過這些案例都是在新堡的煤礦業衰退之後，時值新堡向世界運出最後一船的煤，已然是煉鋁計畫的六年前了。<ref name="russian">[http://archive.thisisthenortheast.co.uk/2004/08/05/43447.html "Taking coals to Newcastle - it finally happens"] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070709145844/http://archive.thisisthenortheast.co.uk/2004/08/05/43447.html |date=2007-07-09 }}, ''[[The_Northern_Echo|The Northern Echo]]'', August 5, 2004</ref>

雖然新堡的煤礦榮景不在，現在應用這句熟語仍不失其字面上的意義，因為澳洲有一個城市名字喚作[[紐卡索|紐卡索]]，即新堡之意。這個澳州的新堡正是因為當地開發出蘊藏量豐富的煤礦，讓當時的歐洲移民起了個相同的名字。<ref name="smh">{{Cite web|url=http://www.smh.com.au/news/new-south-wales/newcastle/2005/02/17/1108500198331.html|title=Newcastle|publisher=[[The_Sydney_Morning_Herald|The Sydney Morning Herald]]|date=2004-02-08|accessdate=2008-09-24|archive-date=2014-06-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140608064059/http://www.smh.com.au/news/New-South-Wales/Newcastle/2005/02/17/1108500198331.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name=tradestats_0708>{{cite web|url=http://www.newportcorp.com.au/client_images/612898.pdf|title=New Trade Record for Newcastle Port|work=Media releases|format=PDF|author=Minister For Ports And Waterways|coauthors=Minister For Regulatory Reform, Minister For Small Business|publisher=[[Newcastle_Port_Corporation|Newcastle Port Corporation]]|date=6 August 2008|accessdate=2008-11-01}}</ref>而澳州新堡亦不負英國新堡的名聲，成為現今世界上煤礦主要供應者。

自從[[全球化|全球化]]的浪潮來襲，也出現不少和運煤到新堡類似的情節，而現在媒體更常用這句話來描述某個初期不被看好的事業，但是最後經營成功的故事。其它的案例還有從[[沙烏地阿拉伯|沙烏地阿拉伯]]出口[[番紅花|番紅花]]到[[印度|印度]]<ref name="saffron">[http://www.time.com/time/asia/features/journey2001/mideast2.html "The Next Asian Journey: Shadows of Old Araby"], ''[[TIME|TIME]]'', vol.158, no.7/8, August 20, 2001</ref>；英國出口[[瑪莎拉雞|瑪莎拉雞]]到[[印度|印度]]<ref name="ctm">[http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/special_report/1999/02/99/e-cyclopedia/1285804.stm "Chicken tikka masala: Spice and easy does it"], ''[[BBC_News|BBC News]]'', April 20, 2001</ref> ；英國出口[[乳酪|乳酪]]和[[香檳酒|香檳酒]]到[[法國|法國]]<ref name="bubbly">"Lovely firm beats French at their own game", ''[[The_Journal_(newspaper)|The Journal]]'', January 27, 2006</ref><ref name="apprentice">[http://www.mirror.co.uk/news/topstories/2007/05/03/french-kiss-off-89520-19036160/ "French Kiss-Off"] {{Webarchive|url=https://archive.today/20070701212840/http://www.mirror.co.uk/news/topstories/2007/05/03/french-kiss-off-89520-19036160/ |date=2007-07-01 }}, ''[[Daily_Mirror|Daily Mirror]]'', May 3, 2007</ref>，還有出口[[漫畫|漫畫]]版的[[莎士比亞|莎士比亞]]作品到[[日本|日本]]<ref name="manga">"Putting the art in the wherefore art", ''[[Cambridge_Evening_News|Cambridge Evening News]]'', May 2, 2007</ref>。

即使地理環境和時代背景都和原先不再相同，這句話仍不退流行。<ref>{{cite web |first1=Michael |last1=Quinion |authorlink=Michael Quinion |work=World Wide Words |url=http://www.goodreads.com/author_blog_posts/1583485-755-1-feedback-notes-and-comments |title=Coals to Newcastle |accessdate=20 October 2013}}</ref>

